      "span_text": "In addition to highlighting the differences between potential benefits for men and women, our analyses demonstrate that risk behavior changes in the form of increases or decreases in condom use may be more or less influential in programs where an intervention can provide a direct benefit to only a fraction of the population (such as the case with male circumcision) versus the entire population (such as the case with HIV vaccines [CITATION_1] ).",
